From 81980ef36c8003d06f54aa8f2eca7ee707810674 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kiro Agent <244629292+kiro-agent@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 05:15:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: resolve 6 critical security vulnerabilities

1. PHI encryption (phi-crypto.ts): Rewrote as server-only module using
   Node.js crypto. Encryption now THROWS when key is missing instead of
   silently storing plaintext. Created /api/phi route for client access.
   Created phi-client.ts with safe masking functions for browser use.

2. Audit log race condition (audit.ts): Hash chain now computed atomically
   via Postgres function with advisory lock (supabase_audit_atomic.sql).
   Client falls back to local mutex if RPC unavailable. All existing
   exports preserved with identical signatures.

3. Rate limiting: Added 3-layer defense - Edge middleware (src/middleware.ts)
   for API routes, reusable rate-limit library (src/lib/rate-limit.ts),
   and client-side limiter in login page (5 attempts/15min, 30min lockout).

4. RLS policies (supabase_rls_policies.sql): Replaced wide-open policies
   with proper role-based access. Deactivated users fully locked out,
   staff cannot modify clinical data, only admin can delete patients or
   view audit logs, billing is tamper-proof after creation.

5. Security headers (next.config.js): Added CSP, X-Frame-Options DENY,
   HSTS, X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy, Permissions-Policy,
   Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy. Removed X-Powered-By. API routes get
   no-cache headers.

Zero TypeScript errors. All existing functionality preserved.
